@@TJvCustomEdit.ProtectPassword
Summary
  Specifies whether to protect the text of the edit control.
Description
  Setting ProtectPassword to true will prevent other programs from access to the text of this edit
  control, and disable altering the PasswordChar.
  
  This is useful if you want the user to enter a password in this edit control, but want to prevent
  possible trojans from retrieving the typed password.

