@@TJvCustomEdit.EmptyValue
Summary
  A text to display when the Text property is empty.
Description
  Use EmptyValue if you want to display a hint to the user when the Text property is empty. As soon
  as the user selects the edit or types some text into the control, the EmptyValue is removed and
  replaced by the new text. If the user clears the content of the edit, the EmptyValue is displayed
  again.
  
  Set EmptyValue to an empty string (the default) to disable this feature.
See Also
  TJvCustomEdit.EmptyFontColor

