@@TJvCustomEdit.AutoHint
Summary
  Specifies whether the control's hint is set to the current text.
Description
  Use AutoHint to indicate whether the text of the control is automatically displayed as the
  control's hint.
  
  If AutoHint is true, the hint is changed according to the following rules:
  
  * If the original hint is non-empty, it is only set if the text doesn't fit in the control. The  
  original hint is automatically restored when the text fits.
  * If the original hint is empty, it is always set to be equivalent to the text.
  Note
  To store a default hint value, AutoUpdate must be set to false.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TControl.Hint>, <DELPHILINK TControl.ShowHint>, <DELPHILINK TControl.Text>

